<P>
   (Coding varies.)
</P>
<P>
   JEWISH-PRESS-MEDIA (Undated) _ Usually, The New York Jewish Week
newspaper, affiliated with the UJA-Federation, sees its job as
putting the Jewish community in a positive light. And so it was a
remarkable departure for the paper to run an extensive
investigative article recently about a local rabbi, the regional
director of the Orthodox Union's summer youth program, who had been
accused for years of sexual improprieties toward teen-age girls.
After the article appeared, the rabbi was fired, despite his
insistence that the accusations were false. The reaction, within
the metropolitan Jewish community, as well as the regional and
national Jewish press, highlights the tension between advocacy and
objectivity in specialized journalism that is aimed at specific
religious, ethnic or cultural groups. By Felicity Barringer.
</P>
<P>
   BOLSTER-PROFILE-MEDIA (Undated) _ Profile of Bill Bolster, the
executive leading CNBC's charge in the TV financial news ratings
battle. By Jim Rutenberg.
</P>
<P>
   MIRRORBALL-TV-MEDIA (Undated) _ The team that produced
``Absolutely Fabulous,'' one of the most successful comedy series
ever imported from England, has created another series that will
have its premiere on the BBC early next year before it eventually
makes its way to two cable channels in the United States, BBC
America and Comedy Central. The show, ``Mirrorball,'' will star
Jennifer Saunders and Joanna Lumley, the two women who also starred
in ``Ab-Fab,'' as the previous hit series came to be called. By
Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   BIG-BROTHER-MEDIA (Undated) _ An update on ``Big Brother''
ratings, through Saturday night. By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   MEDIA-TALK (Undated) _ A ``synergy'' partnership between Talk
magazine and one of its main advertisers is raising eyebrows;
Marian McEvoy, editor-in-chief of Elle Decor and a well-known
figure in the world of design, has been appointed editor-in-chief
of House Beautiful; and Helen Thomas, the longtime White House
correspondent who resigned in April from UPI, has been hired by
Hearst.
</P>
