A7166 &Cx1f; taf-z
u f BC-KETCHUP-KIDS-NYT &LR;      07-09 0325
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KETCHUP-KIDS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HEINZ'S GREEN KETCHUP TARGETS CHILDREN TO BOLSTER SALES GROWTH 
</HEADLINE>
   By CONSTANCE L. HAYS   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In a move to raise sales of its ketchup, H.J. Heinz plans to
introduce a new version Monday that will be bright green and is
intended to appeal to children.
</P>
<P>
   Numerous focus-group sessions with about 1,000 children led
company executives to conclude that ketchup in a new color would
encourage its more liberal use on food. In addition to the green
ketchup, Heinz has also come up with a curvaceous bottle in plastic
it says is softer and easier for children to squeeze. The nozzle
emits a fine stream, compared with previous containers, enabling
children to write their names on their food or play Jackson Pollock
_ parents permitting.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's empowered them in a way that they have always desired but
haven't had an opportunity, until now,'' said Deb Magness, a Heinz
spokeswoman. ``It's a ketchup they can call their own.''
</P>
<P>
   The ketchup, called EZ Squirt, is fortified with Vitamin C and
will start appearing in stores in October, she said. Despite the
color, the vitamins and the packaging, ``there is no taste
difference,'' she added.
</P>
<P>
   With sales of packaged food showing little growth over the last
several years, companies are trying all sorts of strategies to get
their businesses to grow. While new products can increase sales, at
least in the short run, many analysts believe Heinz is likely to
acquire another company so that it can become larger and more
diversified. In addition to ketchup, Heinz also makes pet food,
tuna fish, pickles, private-label soup and other products.
</P>
<P>
   A wave of consolidation during the last three months has paired
Bestfoods with Unilever, and Nabisco with Philip Morris, increasing
the pressure on smaller companies like Heinz to eventually combine
forces with others so that they can be forceful players in the
global supermarket business.
</P>
</TEXT>
