<P>
   LOST-AND-FOUND (Undated) _ The voice on the airport's PA system
is always warning people not to leave their baggage unattended. But
invariably things get left behind as the hordes pass through
Sea-Tac every day on their way to somewhere else. Luckily for
Sea-Tac travelers, the airport has the best lost and found
department and expends the most effort to return items, according
to a recent study by Washington State University. The department is
also staffed by a local non-profit job-training agency working with
low-income people.
</P>
<P>
   By Aliya Saperstein. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-OWEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ The recipe for Low Country Hash
suggests that you run out quickly and purchase three hog heads, 15
pounds of Boston butts, 12 pounds of ears, 12 pounds of tongues and
11 pounds of pork liver. That's just for starters. Sure, it's going
to be a major project. But think of all the leftovers you'll have
to serve your bridge club.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story has moved in the ``d'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ Seattle Mariners host the Los Angeles
Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   By John Hickey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   THIEL-COLUMN (Seattle) _ Art Thiel column on the Mariners.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
